      {
        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "### How many ligands have been studied with both Fe²⁺ and Fe³⁺?\n\n> **94 distinct ligands** appear in the SRD-46 database with stability data for both Fe²⁺ (`metal_62`) and Fe³⁺ (`metal_61`).\n\nFor context: Fe³⁺ has been studied with 406 ligands total, Fe²⁺ with 217 — so the 94 shared ligands represent ~43% of the Fe²⁺ dataset and ~23% of the Fe³⁺ dataset.",
