      {
        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "### Is Fe³⁺ consistently more stable? — Representative Comparison\n\nThe table below shows average log β values (cumulative stability constants) for a selection of the 94 shared ligands, averaged across all reported measurements for each metal.\n\n| Ligand | avg log β (Fe³⁺) | avg log β (Fe²⁺) | Δ log β (Fe³⁺ − Fe²⁺) | Fe³⁺ more stable? |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 2,3-dihydroxybenzoic acid | 43.80 | 10.30 | +33.5 | ✅ |\n| 3,4-dihydroxybenzoic acid | 38.60 | 11.00 | +27.6 | ✅ |\n| hydroxide | 36.81 | 14.50 | +22.3 | ✅ |\n| 8-hydroxyquinoline | 36.40 | 23.40 | +13.0 | ✅ |\n| 5-sulfosalicylic acid | 35.48 | 9.00 | +26.5 | ✅ |\n| acetylacetone | 26.70 | 20.00 | +6.7 | ✅ |\n| citric acid | 25.00 | 15.50 | +9.5 | ✅ |\n| EDTA | 24.86 | 14.28 | +10.6 | ✅ |\n| glycine | 21.00 | 7.60 | +13.4 | ✅ |\n| oxalic acid | 18.49 | 5.22 | +13.3 | ✅ |\n| NTA | 15.87 | 8.84 | +7.0 | ✅ |\n| fluoride | 13.74 | 1.00 | +12.7 | ✅ |\n| malonic acid | 7.30 | 4.70 | +2.6 | ✅ |\n| phosphate | 9.35 | 3.40 | +5.9 | ✅ |\n| **1,10-phenanthroline** | **14.08** | **21.04** | **−6.96** | ❌ Fe²⁺ wins |\n| **2,2'-bipyridine** | **16.31** | **17.22** | **−0.91** | ❌ Fe²⁺ wins |\n| **ethylenediamine** | **7.70** | **9.55** | **−1.85** | ❌ Fe²⁺ wins |",
